  <static seed="135" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring495.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{2t^{2}-18}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>2\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The first thing to observe is that <m>2</m> is common to both 
terms; once we have factored this out, what remains is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {2t^{2}-18} \amp  = 2({t}^2-3^2)\\
                            \amp  = {2\mathopen{}\left(t+3\right)\mathopen{}\left(t-3\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
